<br>
You walk up to the scroll to read it.<br>
It reads as follows.<br>
<br>
The New Combine Empire's purpose.<br>
<br>
New Combine Empire<br>
<br>
<br>
The New Combine Empire was forged out of the <br>
vision of the former Emperor Katta of the old<br>
loyalist Combine Empire.<br>
Mithaniel Marr charged Gavin Steelheart with the<br>
quest to unite people of light and peace so that the <br>
Combine would be born again. <br>
The New Combine values the core beliefs of love<br>
and valor. All races are welcome under the banner<br>
of the New Combine just as the old was.<br>
A new path has changed for the Empire that was once<br>
not possible. Necromancy study under arcane science.<br>
Necromancy will only be taught to a select few within<br>
the empire to teach the rest of the army how to better<br>
defend against such magic.<br>
To learn the true weaknesses and powers it holds.<br>
Dark gods will not be allowed to be worshiped within the<br>
Empire just as it was not before.<br>
The Capitol city of the New Combine resides within<br>
Katta Castellum upon Luclin.<br>
Here is where Emperor Steelheart calls home.<br>
All kingdoms are invited to join the Empire that do not<br>
worship the dark gods as a culture.<br>
If so named kingdoms were to denounce their dark gods<br>
their invitations would be reconsidered.<br>
All kingdoms who have signed the treaty of allegiance <br>
are under the protection of the Empire, under the few conditions such as every Kingdom have an Empire Ambassador assigned to the High Council of Silver Griffons.<br>
The Council will rule as a govern body under the<br>
leadership of an elected Emperor.<br>
If for any circumstance the Emperor should need to be dethroned the Council vote would need to be 70% of the govern body.<br>
The Emperor selected is given a life position. <br>
<br>
Another condition would be to help the Empire as a whole.<br>
As if one city of the Empire was attacked, all others are expected to send help when/if needed.<br>
<br>
Each kingdom within the Empire retains their current system of government. If they have a king, they would still have a king.<br>
Basically the kingdoms of Norrath and Luclin retain their same cultural influences, and laws except where the dark god's influence surfaces.<br>
<br>
The Empire works as a diplomacy tool and way<br>
to protect the whole of the population of Norrath and beyond.<br>
<br>
If a problem occurs within two kingdoms or more and nothing can be settled diplomatically the Emperor must step in and give a fair judgement.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Signed<br>
Emperor Gavin Steelheart<br>
